<div class="page-header"><h1>You do not have to attend ACC to benefit from it</h1>
<p>ACC trains the workforce your community relies on. In-district access means more trained workers, more employer resources, and stronger economic development tools for Pflugerville.</p></div>
<div class="prose">
<h2>The workforce pipeline</h2>
<p>ACC trains nurses, electricians, welders, HVAC technicians, cybersecurity specialists, medical lab techs, advanced manufacturing workers, and more. 80% of ACC graduates stay in Texas. Community college graduates tend to stay within 50 miles of their college. The workforce trained at ACC serves the local economy directly. Source: ACC State of the College 2025; <a href="https://comptroller.texas.gov/economy/economic-data/colleges/texas.php" target="_blank">Texas Comptroller</a>.</p>

<h2>Custom workforce training for businesses</h2>
<p>ACC provides customized workforce training for employers through its Continuing Education division and partnerships with industry. This includes specialized training for local businesses, apprenticeship coordination, and workforce development programs aligned to employer needs. The Lockhart Economic Development Corporation partnered with ACC immediately after annexation to expand vocational training. Pflugerville employers would gain access to the same resources.</p>

<h2>Small business and entrepreneurship</h2>
<p>ACC offers small business development resources, entrepreneurship programs, and business training through ACC Nonprofit Austin and its continuing education division. In-district status means Pflugerville business owners and aspiring entrepreneurs access these resources at lower cost.</p>

<h2>Economic impact: the numbers</h2>
<p>Texas community colleges contribute nearly $10 billion annually to the state economy and support approximately 78,000 jobs. Every dollar spent by Texas community colleges produces an additional $0.86 in economic activity. Every dollar spent on community college compensation produces $0.38 in additional income statewide. Source: <a href="https://comptroller.texas.gov/economy/economic-data/colleges/texas.php" target="_blank">Texas Comptroller</a>.</p>
<p>Workers with some college or an associate degree earn an average of $8,788 more per year than high school diploma holders (BLS, 2024). Over 30 years, that is approximately $264,000 per person. Each additional credential earner in Pflugerville generates local spending, local tax revenue, and demand for local businesses.</p>
<p>Research from the Dallas College Research Institute shows that all large Texas community colleges produce positive total ROI ranging from $771,000 to $1.1 million per student over 40 years. Taxpayer ROI is consistently positive. Source: <a href="https://www.dallascollege.edu/news/2022/the-research-institute-at-dallas-college-launches-tools-to-better-understand-and/" target="_blank">Dallas College Research Institute</a>.</p>

<h2>The opportunity: CTE center and Downtown East</h2>
<p>PfISD is building a new CTE center opening in 2027. The Downtown East development (late 2026/early 2027) creates potential space for ACC to offer local workforce classes. In-district status is the affordability layer that makes these local facilities maximally useful for residents and employers.</p>

